  <front>
    <title>RTP Clock Source Signalling</title>
    <seriesInfo name="Internet-Draft" value="draft-ietf-avtcore-clksrc-04"/>
    <author initials="A." surname="Williams" fullname="Aidan Williams"/>
    <author initials="K." surname="Gross" fullname="Kevin Gross"/>
    <author initials="R." surname="van Brandenburg" fullname="Ray van Brandenburg"/>
    <author initials="H." surname="Stokking" fullname="Hans Stokking"/>
    <date day="08" month="May" year="2013"/>
    <abstract>
      <t>   NTP format timestamps are used by several RTP protocols for
   synchronisation and statistical measurements.  This memo specifies
   SDP signalling identifying timestamp reference clock sources and SDP
   signalling identifying the media clock sources in a multimedia
   session.


	 </t>
    </abstract>
